# Orbis Naming Conventions

## General Principles

- Use **camelCase** for variables, functions, and object properties
- Use **PascalCase** for types, interfaces, classes, and React components
- Use **SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE** for constants and enum-like values
- Use **kebab-case** for file names and URL segments

## Files & Directories

| Type | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| React components | PascalCase | `Globe.tsx`, `PlanetPage.tsx` |
| Hooks | camelCase with `use` prefix | `use-planet-ws.ts`, `usePlanetWebSocket` |
| Utilities/lib | kebab-case or camelCase | `planet-store.ts`, `latlng.ts` |
| Types | colocate with domain | `types.ts` in shared package |

## Identifiers

### Variables & Functions

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
const planetId = "earth-001";
const tileIdFromLatLng = (lat, lng) => ...;
function applyDiff(data) { ... }

// ❌ BAD
const PlanetID = "earth-001";
const tile_id_from_lat_lng = ...;
```

### Types & Interfaces

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - PascalCase, descriptive
interface TileState { ... }
type TreeEntity = ...;
type Biome = "ocean" | "desert" | ...;

// ❌ BAD
interface tile_state { ... }
type tree = ...;
```

### Constants

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
const TILE_SIZE_DEG = 5;
const SMALL_TICK_MS = 2000;
const BIOME_OPTIONS = ["ocean", "desert", ...] as const;
```

## Database

- **Tables**: `snake_case` plural (e.g. `planet_events`, `planet_snapshots`)
- **Columns**: `snake_case` (e.g. `planet_id`, `created_at`, `action_type`)
- **Indexes**: `idx_<table>_<columns>` (e.g. `idx_planet_events_planet_ts`)

## WebSocket Messages

- **Message types**: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` (e.g. `WELCOME`, `SNAPSHOT`, `DIFF`, `INTENT_PLANT_TREE`)
- **Payload keys**: `camelCase` for JSON (e.g. `planetId`, `snapshotVersion`, `tilesChanged`)

## Planet & Entity IDs

- **planetId**: `kebab-case` with optional suffix (e.g. `earth-001`, `mars-001`)
- **Entity IDs**: `type-uuid` (e.g. `tree-abc123`, `struct-xyz789`)
